WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:03.360
Can humans really turn Mars or Venus into a second Earth?

2
00:00:03.360 --> 00:00:04.880
Let's find out.

3
00:00:04.880 --> 00:00:09.120
Terraforming means changing a planet's climate, atmosphere and surface to make it livable

4
00:00:09.120 --> 00:00:10.520
for humans.

5
00:00:10.520 --> 00:00:12.240
Mars sounds like a good option.

6
00:00:12.240 --> 00:00:16.460
It is cold but it has ice, carbon dioxide and Earth-like days.

7
00:00:16.460 --> 00:00:19.000
But the air is much too thin.

8
00:00:19.000 --> 00:00:21.360
There is no magnetic field.

9
00:00:21.360 --> 00:00:24.760
Temperatures can drop to minus 100 degrees Celsius.

10
00:00:24.760 --> 00:00:28.520
Ideas like nuking the poles using giant space mirrors or building greenhouse gas

11
00:00:28.520 --> 00:00:32.040
factories have been proposed but they would take centuries to work.

12
00:00:32.040 --> 00:00:35.760
Venus is the same size as Earth but it is much harsher.

13
00:00:35.760 --> 00:00:39.160
465 degrees Celsius surface temperatures.

14
00:00:39.160 --> 00:00:42.400
92 times Earth's atmospheric pressure.

15
00:00:42.400 --> 00:00:45.000
Toxic clouds of sulfuric acid.

16
00:00:45.000 --> 00:00:49.080
Some say we could cool it down using space umbrellas or even build floating cities high

17
00:00:49.080 --> 00:00:52.080
in the clouds where conditions are more tolerable.

18
00:00:52.080 --> 00:00:54.920
But it is a much bigger challenge than Mars.

19
00:00:54.920 --> 00:00:57.360
So can we terraform these planets?

20
00:00:57.360 --> 00:00:59.080
It's possible in theory.

21
00:00:59.080 --> 00:01:01.400
Way beyond our current technology.

22
00:01:01.400 --> 00:01:04.720
But one day with enough innovation and time who knows?

23
00:01:04.720 --> 00:01:07.120
Want to live on Mars or float above Venus?

24
00:01:07.120 --> 00:01:10.360
Drop your thoughts below and follow for more mind-blowing space facts.

